The plumage is dark[2][7], black or dark brown[5][7]. On the sides of the forehead and on the bridle (the area between the beak and the eye), the tips of the feathers are white[4], there is a black spot behind the eye. Covert feathers of the ear and throat are evenly colored, with the lightest color on the chin[3]. According to many descriptions, the entire head is slightly lighter than the rest of the body, gray or brown[5][7][3]. , the wings are also darker above and lighter under the wing, which is characteristic of all American swifts.